To be defined in detail. Probably simply allowing a few image formats (which are supported by Qt on all platforms) to be added to a schematic, with the following properties:

- Filename (or maybe implicitly using a UUID)
- Position X/Y
- Scale factor

The image file needs to be copied into the project when added to a schematic. Probably it makes sense to copy it into the schematic's directory to maintain a strong relation to the schematic. pull_request.title: Support adding images to symbols & schematics
pull_request.body:
**New features in the symbol- & schematic editors:**

- Add images by choosing a file to load
- Paste images from clipboard (just press Ctrl+V), either from image binary data or a filepath to an image file on disk
- Many image formats are supported, but everything other then SVG, PNG and JPEG will be automatically converted into either PNG or JPEG (using a heuristic to guess the most reasonable format)
- Interactive placement to define position, rotation and scaling of image
- Copy&paste images between symbol- & schematic editors
- Optionally images can have a custom border width specified, to draw a frame around the image (disabled by default, and currently the UI does not yet expose this functionality)
- There's now a new layer "Image Borders" to allow customization of border color
- Include images in PDF/SVG/PNG/etc. export from symbol- or schematic editor, and by output job. The "black/white" setting will convert all images to grayscale and if the background is black, grayscale colors are inverted. The export will report an error if any images could not be loaded.
- Added symbol checks to detect and report invalid images within symbols (e.g. if `symbol.lp` references a nonexistent image file which the user forgot to commit or so).

**Use-cases:**

- Adding diagrams, formulas, tables etc. to schematics
- Adding a company logo to the schematic frame

**File format:**

Any added image will be copied into the symbol directory resp. schematic directory. The filename can be chosen by the user. Only *.svg, *.png and *.jpg are supported by the file format (to keep this feature as portable as possible across platforms) but the editors allow to add images of other formats and automatically perform a conversion before storing.

If the same image is added multiple times to a symbol or schematic, only one file will be added and shared between the instances. The file is automatically deleted if the last instance is removed from a symbol or schematic.
